The paper is primarily focused on algorithmic game theory (AGT), which is a subfield of theoretical computer science. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses reinforcement learning and generative adversarial networks, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new notion of regret and accompanying algorithms, which are related to machine learning and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the application of online monotone game theory to network routing protocols, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
